A desktop scanner that can create detailed 3D computers models of almost any object has gone on sale for £900 ($1,400).

When used with a 3D printer, the Makerbot Digitizer can create anything from toys to practical objects such as furniture, simply by scanning a device that’s already in existence.

The Digitizer, which claims to be able to scan eight inch objects in around 12 minutes, will be shipped to first buyers in October.

