Created by New York-based 3D printing company, Makerbot, the scanner requires no special expertise or 3D modelling software knowledge. 

It works by scanning the contours on the surface of an object using several lasers.

These lasers help capture details as small as 0.5 mm, and surface depth as shallow as 0.5 mm.

The device then turns the data points into a computer model that can be used to replicate the object using a 3D printer.

